title: dataloader test is flaky
body_html:
Seen this twice on contbuilds:

======================================================================
FAIL: test_sequential_batch (__main__.TestDictDataLoader)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "test_dataloader.py", line 252, in test_sequential_batch
    self.assertEqual(set(sample.keys()), {'a_tensor', 'another_dict'})
  File "/home/travis/build/pytorch/pytorch/test/common.py", line 189, in assertEqual
    self.assertEqual(x_, y_, prec, message)
  File "/home/travis/build/pytorch/pytorch/test/common.py", line 186, in assertEqual
    super(TestCase, self).assertEqual(x, y)
AssertionError: 'a_tensor' != 'another_dict'
- a_tensor
+ another_dict
